<TITLE> AL files 4 complaints against BNP, allies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 29 (bdnews24.com)  Awami League has lodged four complaints with the Election Commission against the BNP-led four-party alliance on Monday and demanding immediate action, party leaders said. The allegations of breaching electoral codes include that the BNP chairperson carried out public relations campaigns from Dec. 28 midnight through to the polling day when campaigning was banned. It alleged there was a BNP party slogan at the front of the dais when Khaleda gave her televised address to nation. Some 3,500 observers in Sylhet-1 constituency are BNP supporters, and huge money was splashed out by four-party alliance candidates to buy voters on Sunday night. It demanded immediate withdrawal of those observers from the Sylhet constituency and cancellation of candidacy of those responsible for buying voters. The AL demands also include measures against the BNP chief's public relations campaigns during the prohibited period. A delegation led by AL advisory council member and former secretary Mohammad Ali submitted the written allegations to the EC. The letters of allegations signed by AL election coordination committee co-chairman HT Imam were submitted separately to the EC, delegation members told reporters before leaving the EC secretariat at Sher-e-Bangla Nagar in the city. bdnews24.com
